    <h1>Ludi AI Features Addendum</h1>
    <p><strong>Last updated 19 March 2026.</strong></p>
    <p>
      This Addendum is between Deqo Software Ltd trading as Ludi, a company
      registered in England and Wales under company number 11594409 with its
      registered office at 167–169 Great Portland Street, 5th Floor, London,
      England, W1W 5PF ("<strong>we</strong>", "<strong>us</strong>", or
      "<strong>our</strong>") and the Customer named in this Addendum
      ("<strong>you</strong>" or "<strong>your</strong>"). It forms part of and
      is subject to the terms governing your use of the Ludi platform
      ("<strong>Ludi</strong>"), including our standard Terms of Service or
      service agreement (as applicable), data processing agreement, and our
      Privacy Policy, as may be updated from time to time (together, the
      "<strong>Agreement</strong>").
    </p>
    <p>
      This Addendum supplements the Agreement. In the event of any conflict with
      the Agreement, this Addendum will prevail in respect of AI Features only.
    </p>
    <p>
      Capitalised terms not defined in this Addendum have the meanings given in
      the Agreement.
    </p>

    <h2>1. Definitions</h2>
    <p>In this Addendum, the following terms have the following meanings:</p>
    <p>
      "<strong>AI Features</strong>" has the meaning given to it in clause 2.1;
    </p>
    <p>
      "<strong>Customer Data</strong>" means any data, content or information
      submitted to or processed through the AI Features;
    </p>
    <p>
      "<strong>Data Protection Legislation</strong>" means all applicable
      legislation in force from time to time in the United Kingdom applicable to
      data protection and privacy including, but not limited to, the retained EU
      law version of the General Data Protection Regulation ((EU) 2016/679), as
      it forms part of the law of England and Wales, Scotland, and Northern
      Ireland by virtue of section 3 of the European Union (Withdrawal) Act
      2018) ("<strong>UK GDPR</strong>"); the Data Protection Act 2018 (and
      regulations made thereunder); and the Privacy and Electronic
      Communications Regulations 2003 as amended;
    </p>
    <p>
      "<strong>Input</strong>" means any Customer Data submitted to the AI
      Features;
    </p>
    <p>
      "<strong>Output</strong>" means any content or results generated by the AI
      Features in response to Input; and
    </p>
    <p>
      "<strong>personal data</strong>", "<strong>data controller</strong>",
      "<strong>data processor</strong>", "<strong>special category data</strong>"
      and "<strong>sub-processor</strong>" have the meanings defined in the Data
      Protection Legislation.
    </p>

    <h2>2. Purpose and Scope</h2>
    <p>
      2.1 This Addendum sets out the terms that apply when you choose to use
      AI-powered features within Ludi ("<strong>AI Features</strong>"). The AI
      Features use large language models (LLMs) and related artificial
      intelligence technologies to assist with collaboration, analysis,
      reporting, and automation in your workspace.
    </p>
    <p>2.2 AI Features may include, without limitation:</p>
    <ul role="list">
      <li>grouping, summarising, or analysing Board content;</li>
      <li>generating meeting notes or session reports;</li>
      <li>generating content;</li>
      <li>
        detecting patterns, themes, or sentiment across boards, users, or teams;
      </li>
      <li>producing benchmarks, insights, or usage statistics;</li>
      <li>
        generating or configuring boards or templates based on User input; and
      </li>
      <li>
        other evolving AI-driven functionality intended to enhance the product
        experience.
      </li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      2.3 Use of AI Features is entirely optional and available only to
      Subscribers who explicitly opt in.
    </p>
    <p>
      2.4 AI Features form part of the Services provided under the Agreement and
      remain subject to the Agreement, including any applicable limitations of
      liability.
    </p>
    <p>
      2.5 We may modify, restrict, or withdraw AI Features at any time, acting
      reasonably and in accordance with the Agreement.
    </p>

    <h2>3. Data Processing and Sub-Processors</h2>
    <p>
      3.1 When enabled, AI Features may send certain Customer Data to
      sub-processors for processing. The categories of data that may be
      processed include:
    </p>
    <ul role="list">
      <li>
        <strong>Board Content</strong> – Content created or generated on a Board;
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Person Identifiers</strong> – user name, email address, user ID,
        or profile picture;
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Board Metadata</strong> – Board name, creation and update
        timestamps; and
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Team and Company Data</strong> – team and company names, IDs, and
        related metadata.
      </li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      3.2 To the extent that Customer Data includes personal data, we act as a
      data processor and process such personal data in accordance with Data
      Protection Legislation and any applicable data processing terms forming
      part of the Agreement. This Addendum supplements (and does not replace)
      such data processing terms and we will implement appropriate technical and
      organisational measures to protect such personal data in line with our
      standard security practices.
    </p>
    <p>
      3.3 You must ensure that your use, and the use by Users under your
      Account, of AI Features complies with Data Protection Legislation, and you
      must ensure and procure that Users do not upload or include any sensitive
      or special category data unless expressly agreed in writing with us. AI
      Features are not designed for such data.
    </p>
    <p>
      3.4 We may use one or more of the following sub-processors to provide the
      AI Features:
    </p>
    <ul role="list">
      <li>
        <strong>Anthropic PBC</strong><br />
        <a href="mailto:legal@anthropic.com">legal@anthropic.com</a><br />
        <a
          href="https://www.anthropic.com/legal/data-processing-addendum"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener">Data Processing Addendum</a
        >
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Google Cloud AI (Google LLC)</strong><br />
        <a href="mailto:legal-notices@google.com">legal-notices@google.com</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://cloud.google.com/terms/data-processing-addendum"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener">Data Processing Addendum</a
        >
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>OpenAI, L.L.C.</strong><br />
        <a href="mailto:legalprivacy@openai.com">legalprivacy@openai.com</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://openai.com/policies/data-processing-addendum/"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener">Data Processing Addendum</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      3.5 Each sub-processor acts solely on our documented instructions and is
      bound by appropriate contractual safeguards, including where applicable the
      EU Standard Contractual Clauses and/or the UK International Data Transfer
      Addendum, in each case where applicable.
    </p>
    <p>
      3.6 We will maintain and update our list of sub-processors from time to
      time. We will give you reasonable advance notice of any changes to the
      sub-processors. If you reasonably object to the use of certain
      sub-processors, you may disable the AI Features through your Account.
    </p>
    <p>
      3.7 We do not use Customer Data to train our own AI models. Third party AI
      providers may process Customer Data in accordance with their own terms, as
      made available to you.
    </p>
    <p>
      3.8 You acknowledge that AI Features may be susceptible to misuse,
      including prompt injection or other malicious inputs, and you must not
      knowingly input or submit any Content intended to manipulate, disrupt or
      extract data from the AI Features or underlying systems.
    </p>

    <h2>4. Customer API Keys</h2>
    <p>
      4.1 You may choose to use your own API credentials for one or more
      supported AI providers. When doing so, you act as the data controller for
      all personal data processed through that API key, and we act only on your
      lawful and reasonable instructions as a data processor.
    </p>
    <p>
      4.2 You are solely responsible for your use of any third party AI
      provider, including compliance with its terms and Data Protection
      Legislation.
    </p>
    <p>
      4.3 To the extent permitted by law, we bear no responsibility or liability
      for processing carried out via API keys that you have supplied.
    </p>

    <h2>5. Pricing and Availability</h2>
    <p>
      5.1 Use of AI Features is subject to pricing, plan and term eligibility
      determined by us from time to time.
    </p>
    <p>
      5.2 Current pricing and applicable usage limits may be made available on
      request or published within Ludi or related materials.
    </p>
    <p>
      5.3 We may modify such pricing, limits, or availability in accordance with
      the Agreement, and continued use of AI Features after any change
      constitutes acceptance of the updated terms.
    </p>

    <h2>6. Use Restrictions and Customer Responsibilities</h2>
    <p>
      6.1 You must not, and you must ensure and procure that Users do not, use
      AI Features:
    </p>
    <ul role="list">
      <li>in breach of any applicable law or regulation;</li>
      <li>
